In [[economics]], the '''weak axiom of cost minimization''' ('''WACM''') provides a non-parametric test of [[Cost-minimization analysis|cost minimization]], which can be applied only when both input price and quantity data are available for individual firms.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Ray |first=S.C. |title=Weak Axiom of Cost Dominance: A Nonparametric Test of Cost Efficiency Without Input Quantity Data |url=http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/klu/prod/1997/00000008/00000002/00131288 |journal=Journal of Productivity Analysis |volume=8 |number=2, 15 |publisher=Springer |date=May 1997 |pages=151–165}}</ref>

